caption: Table 1: Comparison of time complexity in the augmentation Phase. n denotes the size of the graph.
description: This table compares the time complexity of the augmentation phase for four different graph contrastive learning models: SPAN, JOAO, AD-GCL, and the proposed GOUDA.  The time complexity is expressed in Big O notation as a function of the number of nodes (n), number of edges (m), dimension of attributes (f), and dimension of hidden layers (d). The table shows that GOUDA has a lower time complexity than the other three models, making it more efficient for large graphs.
